Machine Learning Regression Suite

Overview
This repository demonstrates foundational regression techniques in Machine Learning, focusing on practical implementation and conceptual clarity.
The work covers:
•	Simple Linear Regression (SLR)
•	Multiple Linear Regression (MLR)
•	Feature Selection & Impact Analysis
•	Model Evaluation using Train-Test methodology
Each implementation is structured to reflect real-world problem-solving approaches.
________________________________________
Modules
01. House Price Prediction — (Simple Linear Regression)
A univariate regression model designed to predict housing prices based on property size.
Objective:
Establish a linear relationship between a single independent variable and the target.
________________________________________
02. Employee Performance Prediction — (Multiple Linear Regression)
A multivariate model leveraging professional attributes such as experience and training duration to estimate performance ratings.
Objective:
Understand how multiple factors collectively influence the output variable.
________________________________________
03. Student Performance Analysis — (Feature Sensitivity Study)
A regression model integrating academic and behavioral factors, along with an intentionally irrelevant feature, to evaluate feature impact.
Objective:
Analyze the effect of meaningful vs non-meaningful features on model performance.
________________________________________
Methodology
Each module follows a consistent workflow:
•	Data Structuring
•	Feature–Target Segregation
•	Train-Test Splitting
•	Model Training (Linear Regression)
•	Performance Evaluation
________________________________________
Key Learnings
•	Clear distinction between SLR and MLR
•	Importance of feature selection in predictive modeling
•	Identification of noise vs signal in datasets
•	Understanding model generalization vs overfitting risks
•	Evaluation through training and testing performance metrics
